                  </persName>
            .</p>
               <p>JOHN BROWN. I am servant to Mr. William Haskins, who is a <rs id="t18170521-151-viclabel777" type="occupation">jeweller</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18170521-151-victim897 t18170521-151-viclabel777"></join>, and lives in <placeName id="t18170521-151-crimeloc778">St. Martin's-court</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18170521-151-crimeloc778" type="placeName" value="St. Martin's-court"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18170521-151-crimeloc778" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18170521-151-off775 t18170521-151-crimeloc778"></join>. On the 19th of May, about eight o'clock in the evening, the prisoner came into the shop, and asked for a sixpenny row of beads. I took them from the door, and he picked out a row - I hung them up again. He walked about the door, backward and forward - I lost him all in a minute, and was told the beads were taken from the door. I am sure he is the man.</p>
               <p>JOHN ANDERSON. I live next door to Mr. Haskins, and watched the prisoner lurking about the door, and saw him take a quantity of beads off the door-post - He put them in a handkerchief and ran off with them. I told the constable - I am sure he is the man.</p>
               <p>THOMAS COOK. I am a constable. Anderson described the prisoner to me, but I could not find him; I told Anderson to keep a look-out, the next day he sent for me, and pointed the prisoner out - I secured him, and asked him where the beads were? he said he never had any, but admitted having been to the shop.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18170521-151-verdict779" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18170521-151-verdict779" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 30.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18170521-151-punish780" type="punishmentDescription">
